  {
    "html": "<div style=\"position:relative;width:100%;height:100%;background:var(--surface-dark);background-color:var(--surface-dark);overflow:hidden;\">\n            <div style=\"position: absolute; pointer-events: none; background: var(--texture-grain); opacity: 0.04; z-index: 1; inset: 0\"></div>\n            \n            <div class=\"slide-content\" style=\"position:relative;z-index:10;padding:80px 48px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;height:100%;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;overflow:hidden;\">\n                <div style=\"width:100%;\"><h2 style=\"font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.18; color: #E8F1EF; margin: 0 0 16px; text-align: left; letter-spacing: -0.01em; overflow-wrap: break-word\">Myth vs Fact</h2><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;width:100%;\"><div style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:0;padding:14px 18px;margin-bottom:12px;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);position:relative;flex-shrink:0;\">\n                    <div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#C4D1CE;text-decoration:line-through;text-decoration-color:#429687;text-decoration-thickness:2px;opacity:0.6;line-height:1.35;\">Good design is what makes carousels work</div>\n                    <div style=\"position:absolute;top:50%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%) rotate(-6deg);font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:10px;font-weight:800;color:#000302;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;background:#429687;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:20px;box-shadow:0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);\">MYTH</div>\n                </div><div style=\"background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border-left:4px solid #429687;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-left-width:4px;border-radius:0;padding:14px 18px;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);flex-shrink:0;\">\n                    <div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:10px;font-weight:800;color:#429687;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px;\">FACT</div>\n                    <div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:#E8F1EF;line-height:1.35;\">Good narrative structure is what makes carousels work. Design is the vehicle, not the engine.</div>\n                </div><div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:13px;color:#C4D1CE;margin-top:14px;line-height:1.45;\">The highest-performing carousels often have simple, even plain design. What they have is a relentless emotional arc that carries the viewer from hook to action.</div></div></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>",
